The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) National Youth Vanguard has asked the National Working Committee (NWC) of the party to forward the nomination of Senator Suleiman Nazif Gamawa to the National Executive Committee (NEC) for ratification as the new Deputy National Chairman (North). The office of PDP Deputy National Chairman (North) has been vacant since February 2019 following the suspension and subsequent expulsion of Senator Babayo Garba Gamawa from the party who later died. Addressing a press conference yesterday in Abuja, the National Coordinator of the PDP Youth Vanguard, Ambassador Ibrahim Bala Aboki, advised the NWC to take appropriate steps in order to ensure the office didnâ€™t remain vacant for too long. PDP youths want Nazif as deputy national chairman PDP suspends Babayo Gamawa, deputy chair, North PDP suspends Secondus' deputy over 'anti-party' activities Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.